description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic organised person to join our Cardiology team in Wrexham Maelor Hospital, to assist in the smooth running of our clinics and the pathways of our patients with a variety of administrative duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant needs to have a knowledge and understanding of Cardiology pathways in addition to experience with basic administrative duties to be able to assist the department in preparing clinics, chasing and inputting patient outcomes, locating and tracking case notes and liaising with medical secretaries, operational teams and other professionals. They should have good organisational, communication, time management and computer skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working hours are 27.5 hours per week, Monday to Friday, negotiable to cover service requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 11/11/20&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKristina BatesJob titleAssistant Operational ManagerEmail addresskristina.bates@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number03000 858405&lt;/p&gt;
